sec.p:
Two new species of
Dasybasis Macquart
from the Peruvian Andes of Cusco ( Diptera : Tabanidae : Diachlorini )

Three subfamilies and nine tribes of horse flies are found in South America. The tabanid tribe Diachlorini ( Tabanidae , Tabaninae), the most diverse tribe in the family, occurs mostly in the Australasian and Neotropical regions. More than half of the species in the tribe occur in the Neotropical region, where 594 of the 1,205 species and 41 genera of 75 genera are Diachlorini (
; tatus,
).

